X_1, X_2, ..., X_n
E(X_1+X_2+ \cdots +X_k \mid X_1+X_2+ \cdots +X_n=b)=b \cdot \frac{k}{n} .
k = 1
X_i
i
1 \le i \le n
 \mathbb E(X_i \, | \, X_1 + \dots + X_n = b ) 
 n \, \mathbb E \left( X_i \, \left| \sum_{i=1}^n X_i = b \right. \right)   = \sum_{i=1}^n \, \mathbb E \left(X_i \, \left| \, \sum_{i=1}^n X_i = b \right. \right) = \mathbb E \left( \sum_{i=1}^n X_i \, \left| \, \sum_{i=1}^n X_i = b \right. \right) = b 
 \mathbb E \left( X_i \, \left| \sum_{i=1}^n X_i = b \right. \right) = \frac bn. 
